gsonpath

Class GsonPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • gsonpath.GsonPath

  • public class GsonPath
extends java.lang.Object
    The primary class to use when using the GsonPath library.

    It supplies factories which expose auto generated class created using the AutoGsonAdapter and AutoGsonArrayStreamer annotations.

    • Method Detail

      • createTypeAdapterFactory

        public static GsonPathTypeAdapterFactory createTypeAdapterFactory()
        Creates an instance of the GsonPathTypeAdapterFactory class.

        This factory is used to map the auto generated TypeAdapter classes created using the AutoGsonAdapter annotation.

        Only a single use of reflection is used within the constructor, so it isn't critical to hold onto this reference for later usage.

      • getGsonArrayStreamerFactory

        public static GsonArrayStreamerFactory getGsonArrayStreamerFactory()
        Creates an instance of the GsonArrayStreamerFactory class.

        This factory is used to map the auto generated GsonArrayStreamer classes created using the AutoGsonArrayStreamer annotation.

        Only a single use of reflection is used within the constructor, so it isn't critical to hold onto this reference for later usage.

      • getArrayStreamer

        public static <T extends GsonArrayStreamer> T getArrayStreamer(java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Creates an instance of the GsonArrayStreamerFactory class and returns a generated implementation of a GsonArrayStreamer for a given class type which must implement GsonArrayStreamer.

        See the getGsonArrayStreamerFactory() documentation for further details.
